{"title": "Chouans (version 2)", "description": "\u201cThe Chouans\u201d (1829) was the first novel published under Balzac\u2019s own name (rather than a pen-name). It became the first book in the great work of his lifetime \u2014 the novel series titled \u201cThe Human Comedy.\u201d<br><br>\r\n\r\nBalzac was impressed by the writings of Sir Walter Scott. Scott made Scottish history come alive by creating fictions that used real history as backdrop. Balzac\u2019s novel is set in 1799 \u2014 the year that Napoleon became First Consul of France. In the far west of France (i.e., Brittany), anti-revolutionary sentiment still simmered. The Chouans were a rustic guerrilla militia who wanted to undo the French Revolution and restore the old Bourbon monarchy. Pitted against them were the forces of the new Republic and its military (\u201cthe Blues\u201d). Balzac researched this historical period as well as living conditions for Bretons of that time, then wove into the actual history his own fictional account of a romance between lovers from opposite factions in the dispute.<br><br>\r\n\r\nIn \u201cThe Chouans,\u201d we see an early and influential example of \u201chistorical fiction,\u201d a genre which blossomed in popularity during the 1800s, and remains popular in today\u2019s novels and films. - Summary by Bruce Pirie", "duration": 57330, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "86", "name": "Honor\u00e9 de Balzac"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/chouans_2212_librivox/chouans2_2022.jpg", "copyright_year": "1901", "genres": ["Historical Fiction", "Literary Fiction", "Published 1800 -1900"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Bruce Pirie"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Bruce Pirie"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "redrun"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1.a  The Ambuscade", "readers": [3699], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/chouans_2212_librivox/chouans_01_bal